Wizards are formal arcane casters from the Axiomatic Schools, founded on replicable methodology after the Spirebound Conclave's catastrophe.
Core principle: magical phenomena are real, consistent, and subject to formal analysis with independently verifiable results.
A procedure that cannot be reliably replicated is either documented incorrectly or is not a genuine phenomenon.
The Artificers of Sequence applied formal proof to combat casting: sequence optimization under uncertainty for maximum effect at minimum cost.
Combat role is methodical arcane caster emphasizing accurate assessment before engagement and optimal spell sequencing.
Training emphasizes problem-solving methodology rather than fixed sequences. Internalized methodology beats memorized solutions.
Wizards command exactitude and sequence. Sorcerers command breadth and synthesis.
The Wizard's Keep drew substantially on Axiomatic methodology for its Triple-Ledger governance.
The Grand Magi class synthesizes the Wizard (Axiomatic Schools) and Sorcerer (Chromatic Circle) approaches.
